---

Wash and dry produce. Cut @grilling cheese{6%ounce} into four large pieces (eight pieces for
4 servings). Trim and quarter @zucchini{1}(trimmed and quartered lengthwise); cut crosswise
into 1/2-inch-thick quarter-moons.

Place @Za'atar spice{1%tablespoon} on a #plate{}. Working one at a time, press cheese pieces
into Za'atar spice until fully coated.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{} in a large, preferably nonstick, #pan{} over medium-high heat
(for 4, use a large, high-sided pan). Add cheese and cook until browned, ~{1-2%minutes} per
side (while the cheese cooks, discard any remaining Za'atar spice from plate; reserve plate).

Turn off heat. Transfer cheese to plate used for spice. Reserve pan.

Heat another drizzle of @cooking oil{} in pan used for cheese over medium-high heat. Add
zucchini; cook, stirring occasionally, until beginning to brown, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Massage @microwavable grain blend{1} in package to separate grains.

Reduce heat under pan to medium. Add grain blend, @Vidalia onion paste{1/2%ounce}, and
@veggie stock concentrate{1} to pan with zucchini. Stir to combine. Cook, stirring
occasionally, until zucchini is tender and grains are warmed through, ~{1-2%minutes}.

> If grains begin to pop, cover pan with a #lid{}.

Remove pan from heat and add @romesco sauce{6%tablespoon}; stir to combine. Taste and
season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Divide zucchini and grains between shallow #bowls{}. Drizzle with @yogurt{4%tablespoon}.
Top with grilling cheese. Serve.